		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Non-linear editing system</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<dl>
<dd><i>"NLE" redirects here. For the standardized test, see <a href="/wiki/National_Latin_Examination" title="National Latin Examination" class="mw-redirect">National Latin Examination</a>.</i></dd>
</dl>
<p>A <b>non-linear editing system</b> (<b>NLE</b>) is a <a href="/wiki/Video_editing" title="Video editing">video editing</a> (NLVE) or <a href="/wiki/Audio_editing" title="Audio editing" class="mw-redirect">audio editing</a> (NLAE) system which can perform <a href="/wiki/Random_access" title="Random access">random access</a> on the source material.</p>
